{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17601016","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17601016"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:09:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:09:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15643"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15643"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8334"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62131"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8334"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15643"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47577"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2994"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5295"},{"type":"tags","id":"10150"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20104"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20107"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62131","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62131"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECortisol secretion follows a distinct daily pattern regulated by the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis and circadian rhythm.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following times represents the typical peak in cortisol levels?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["8 pm","12 am","4 am","8 am","6 pm"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECortisol follows a circadian rhythm with levels beginning to rise around 2-3 am, reaching peak concentrations at \u003Cstrong\u003E8 am\u003C/strong\u003E. This morning peak helps prepare the body for daily activities. Levels gradually decline throughout the day, with lowest concentrations around \u003Cstrong\u003E12 am\u003C/strong\u003E midnight.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe timing is important because:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EAt \u003Cstrong\u003E4 am\u003C/strong\u003E, levels are rising but have not yet peaked\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EBy \u003Cstrong\u003E6 pm\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003E8 pm\u003C/strong\u003E, levels have significantly decreased as part of the natural daily rhythm\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThis pattern can be disrupted in shift workers and during jet lag\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EUnderstanding this rhythm is crucial for timing glucocorticoid replacement therapy\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cortisol follows a circadian rhythm with peak levels occurring in early morning around 8am","The cortisol awakening response helps prepare the body for daily activities by increasing alertness and metabolism"],"references":["Knezevic E, Nenic K, Milanovic V, Knezevic NN. The Role of Cortisol in Chronic Stress, Neurodegenerative Diseases, and Psychological Disorders. Cells. 2023 Nov 29;12(23):2726. doi: 10.3390/cells12232726. PMID: 38067154; PMCID: PMC10706127.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford Uni